President Trump hosted a showcase of American small businesses at the White House, where he announced that the US economy added almost 5 million new jobs in June. He highlighted that this is the largest monthly jobs gain in history and shattered all expectations and records. He emphasized the gains made by African American and Hispanic workers, and praised the resilience and craftsmanship of American small businesses. President Trump also discussed the efforts being made to combat the coronavirus, including the development of therapeutics and vaccines through Operation Warp Speed. He expressed optimism about the future of the economy and urged the nation to renew its devotion to American values. The President also mentioned his upcoming visit to Mount Rushmore and praised law enforcement and the military for their efforts in maintaining law and order.